flowchart LR

  subgraph INTENT["1. Path objective"]
    G1["Turn a run from eligible-to-become-ready into authoritatively declared ready"]
    G2["Make readiness a formal closure point rather than a soft health signal"]
    G3["Keep readiness under control-plane authority rather than letting compute alone close the gate"]
  end

  subgraph ENTRY["2. Entry basis"]
    E1["The entry is not 'the stream lane looks healthy'"]
    E2["SR joins and replay prerequisites already pass"]
    E3["The control-topic contract is already pinned"]
    E4["The required ready-closure handle set is resolved"]
    E5["The Step Functions authority surface resolves to a real active state machine"]
    E6["Prechecks validate run-continuity handoff, Step Functions handle chain, and control-topic anchors before READY publication"]
  end

  subgraph SPINE["5. Broad route logic"]
    R1["SR prerequisites satisfied"]
    R2["READY computed and published on the control bus"]
    R3["Step Functions commits READY as control authority"]
    R4["Durable READY receipt becomes the authoritative proof"]
    R5["Authoritatively ready run"]
  end

  subgraph CARRIES["4. What the path carries"]
    C1["Run identity:<br/>platform_run_id + scenario_run_id"]
    C2["Run-scoped READY publication controls:<br/>READY message filter + control-topic partitioning key"]
    C3["The READY signal itself"]
    C4["The Step Functions execution reference that makes the receipt authoritative"]
    C5["Run-scoped identity continuity across orchestrator transitions and evidence emission"]
  end

  subgraph LOGIC["6. Logical design reading"]
    L1["This path shows that the platform treats readiness as an authorization problem, not just a liveness problem"]
    L2["The platform does not say 'the lane emitted something, therefore we are ready'"]
    L3["A run becomes ready only when the control plane records READY through the pinned authority"]
    L4["Single-active-path law is part of that authorization story"]
    L5["This makes the current wired system look governed rather than improvised"]
  end

  subgraph SEATING["7. Concrete seating in the current wired system"]
    S1["Control surface: Kafka control topic"]
    S2["Control-plane authority: Step Functions state machine fraud-platform-dev-full-platform-run-v0"]
    S3["READY receipt lands under the run's S3 evidence root"]
    S4["READY_MESSAGE_FILTER = platform_run_id=={platform_run_id}"]
    S5["KAFKA_PARTITION_KEY_CONTROL = platform_run_id"]
    S6["SR_READY_COMMIT_RECEIPT_PATH_PATTERN = evidence/runs/{platform_run_id}/sr/ready_commit_receipt.json"]
    S7["The path is concretely realized in control topic, state machine, and S3 receipt surfaces"]
  end

  subgraph RATIONALE["8. Why the design looks like this"]
    Y1["Flink-ready output implicitly closing the gate was rejected"]
    Y2["Dynamic runtime fallback mid-phase for convenience was rejected"]
    Y3["Both were rejected because they weaken deterministic gate closure, evidence attribution, and auditable control-plane ownership"]
    Y4["So Step Functions remains the sole READY commit authority and the path stays single and explicit during the phase"]
    Y5["When READY publication initially failed, the remediation did not weaken the proof rule, fake a receipt, or shift authority"]
    Y6["The system used bounded diagnostics, fixed the publisher defect, and then proved READY publication and receipt cleanly"]
    Y7["The path design was preserved under friction rather than diluted"]
  end

  subgraph CONTRACT["9. What larger contracts are shaping this path"]
    X1["The main shaping pressure is the platform's own control and evidence law"]
    X2["The run-process requires explicit PASS gates and durable commit evidence for closure"]
    X3["The design authority requires one active runtime path per phase and forbids in-phase switching"]
    X4["The design authority also requires Step Functions-backed run-state orchestration"]
    X5["The observability contract requires run-scoped correlation across orchestrator transitions and evidence surfaces"]
    X6["This path is shaped by platform governance law, not just local runtime behavior"]
  end

  subgraph TRADEOFFS["10. Trade-offs and constraints"]
    T1["This path deliberately adds ceremony and friction"]
    T2["READY cannot be implied"]
    T3["Closure needs a control topic, run-scoped filter, Step Functions execution reference, duplicate and ambiguity checks, and durable evidence"]
    T4["This is more demanding than a looser design"]
    T5["The cost buys deterministic gate ownership and cleaner replay/audit semantics"]
    T6["Even publish-path defects had to be fixed without bypassing the same authority and evidence model"]
  end

  subgraph NECESSITY["11. Necessity test"]
    N1["Without this path, the platform can still have running components and source-realized data"]
    N2["But it loses a clean answer to: who said this run was ready, and what makes that claim authoritative?"]
    N3["Readiness collapses into a vague runtime feeling"]
    N4["The platform loses deterministic READY ownership"]
    N5["The committed ready receipt disappears"]
    N6["Duplicate and ambiguity discipline disappear"]
    N7["The boundary between compute output and control-plane authorization disappears"]
    N8["That weakens A immediately because the system becomes hand-wavy at the moment it claims to become operational"]
  end

  subgraph CLOSURE["3. Owned outcome and 12. What this path proves for A"]
    O1["READY emitted to the control topic"]
    O2["READY receipt committed with a Step Functions execution reference"]
    O3["Duplicate or ambiguous READY absent"]
    O4["Authority proven to be Step Functions"]
    O5["Owned outcome: an authoritatively ready run, not merely a computed readiness hint"]
    O6["Later gate advance is downstream consequence, not the primary owned closure of this path"]
    A1["Purpose claim:<br/>the platform has a dedicated job for authorizing readiness"]
    A2["Intentionality claim:<br/>the route is deliberately control-plane-backed, with Step Functions as sole commit authority"]
    A3["Materialization claim:<br/>the path is concretely seated in the control topic, state machine, and S3 receipt surfaces"]
    A4["Constraint-awareness claim:<br/>the design knowingly rejects Flink-only closure and in-phase switching because they would weaken evidence attribution"]
    A5["Quantified closure claim:<br/>all required ready-closure handles resolved;<br/>authority surface active;<br/>authoritative READY commit closed green with zero blockers before rollup advanced"]
    A6["A-level meaning:<br/>'this run is now ready' becomes an explicit, control-plane-owned, durable fact rather than an inferred compute-side feeling"]
  end

